I enjoyed participating in this study.

Moral obligation is a myth: nobody is obligated to do anything. I'm a bleeding-heart communist who advocates for the life and limb of our natural world and those around me because a rising tide lifts all ships-- most importantly, mine-- not because I feel some sort of ""obligation"" to take the apparatus of choice away from me.

I have been told by a doctor that I need to eat meat for health reasons since I become deficient in nutrients when I do not eat meat. I also was diagnosed with the eating disorder ""Orthorexia Nervosa"" where my main symptom was restricting meat and dairy. I was forced to go through an eating disorder recovery program because of this. (It's a bit triggering for me to be asked to eat less meat). This was a good study, I just know that I cannot eat any less meat.

I find it a bit amusing that you asked about our willingness to eat a range of percentages less of meat, YET you totally forgot to ask if we eat ANY meat all!
